Data Transfer Object (DTO)


Intent:
    Bundle the required data that must be tranferred from one process to another

When:
    Reduce process interaction overhead
    - result in network transfer reduction
    - Avoid transferring extra unwanted data, that may be the result of interface design

Structure:
    - data
    - getData()
    - setData()

Benefits:
    - when correctly applied it gives you a performance boost
    - You can limit the need to know data

Drawbacks:
    - Creating and maintaining transfer objects

Conclusion:
    Data Tranfer Object is great
    - Focus on data that must be transferred
    - Improve data transfer of service oriented applications